Population 1: age 0-5 Population 2: age 6-12 Population 3: age 13-20

The literature reflects that fluoride varnish when applied to the teeth of high-risk children, reduces, in conjunction with anticipatory guidance provided to the caregiver, the risk of the child developing caries.

ADA Clinical recommendations for use of professionally applied or prescription-strength:
- Younger Than 6 Years - 2.26 percent fluoride varnish at least every three to six months
- 6-18 Years - 2.26 percent fluoride varnish at least every three to six Months OR 1.23 percent fluoride (APF*) gel for four minutes at least every three to six months
- Older Than 18 Years - 2.26 percent fluoride varnish at least every three to six months OR 1.23 percent fluoride (APF) gel for four minutes at least every three to six months.
A higher score indicates better quality
JA. Wentraub, F. Ramos-Gomez, B. Jue, S. Shain, CI. Hoover, JDB. Featherstone, and SA. Gansky. Fluoride Varnish Efficacy in Prevention ECC. J Dent Res 85(2): 172-176, 2006.
